.SH NAME
distill-ai - distill-ai — compress logs and test output for LLM consumption


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdistill-ai [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
distill-ai is a Unix filter that distills noisy command output
(test runs, application logs, stack traces) into a compact,
structured form suitable for LLM context windows or human triage.

.PP
The default invocation (\fBcmd | distill-ai\fR) reads from stdin,
autodetects the format, and emits the distilled stream to stdout.
Use the 'run' subcommand explicitly when you want positional FILE
arguments and an explicit FORMAT.

.PP
This is an early development build. Several flags are registered but
not yet plumbed; their help text says "(plumbing lands in M8.x)".
See ARCHITECTURE.md and TODO.md for the roadmap.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--auto\fP[=true]
	Autodetect the input format from a sample of the input. Pass --auto=false with a positional FORMAT to skip detection.

.PP
\fB--budget\fP=0
	Target output token cost. Zero means no cap. Drops or truncates lower-severity events to fit; exit code 3 reports drops.

.PP
\fB--config\fP=""
	Path to a TOML configuration file. Overrides automatic discovery (no project walk, no user config).

.PP
\fB--context\fP=0
	Lines of context around each event. Zero means format-default (3 for 'generic').

.PP
\fB--dedupe\fP[=false]
	Enable LRU deduplication of identical events. Default window is 1024; override with --dedupe-window.

.PP
\fB--dedupe-window\fP=-1
	LRU capacity for dedupe. Negative means 'pick a default based on --dedupe / --no-dedupe'; 0 disables dedupe; positive enables with that capacity.

.PP
\fB--explain\fP[=false]
	Dry-run mode: annotate which events were kept or dropped and why, without distilled output. Equivalent to the 'explain' subcommand; the flag is registered for convenience but the subcommand is preferred.

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for distill-ai

.PP
\fB--keep-vendor\fP[=false]
	Leave vendor / stdlib stack frames in the output instead of collapsing them.

.PP
\fB--keep-warnings\fP[=false]
	Include warnings alongside errors. Per-format opt-in; honoured by 'generic' as of M9.4.

.PP
\fB--list-formats\fP[=false]
	List every registered format and exit. (Equivalent to the 'list-formats' subcommand; plumbing lands in M8.4.)

.PP
\fB--max-events\fP=0
	Cap the total number of events emitted. Zero means no cap. Applied after --budget so the budget enforcer's severity-priority truncation runs first.

.PP
\fB--no-dedupe\fP[=false]
	Disable LRU deduplication. Wins over --dedupe when both are set.

.PP
\fB--no-footer\fP[=false]
	Suppress the trailing 'collapsed X, dropped Y' summary. (Ignored by --output=json; the summary is part of the schema.)

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output encoder: text | json | markdown.

.PP
\fB--output-streaming\fP[=false]
	Emit ndjson with a trailing summary line instead of a single batch object. Only affects --output=json.

.PP
\fB--passthrough\fP[=false]
	If no events were found, emit the input unchanged instead of an empty stream. Exit code stays 0. Buffers the input in memory.

.PP
\fB--print-config\fP[=false]
	Print the merged effective configuration as TOML and exit. Useful for debugging which config or flag is winning.

.PP
\fB--severity\fP=""
	Minimum severity to keep (error|warn|info). Empty means format-default (error). Per-format opt-in; honoured by 'generic' as of M9.4.

.PP
\fB--strict\fP[=false]
	Fail with exit code 2 when autodetect can't pick a specific format with confidence ≥ 0.6.

.PP
\fB--strip-envelope\fP="auto"
	Strip CI / orchestrator envelope before format detection: auto (detect a registered stripper; default), none (pass bytes through unchanged), or the name of a specific stripper (e.g. github-actions, gitlab-ci once those land in M13.3 / M13.4).

.PP
\fB--tokenizer\fP="heuristic"
	Token estimator used by --budget: heuristic | tiktoken. heuristic is fast and zero-dep; tiktoken is exact for OpenAI / Claude models.

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	Write pipeline diagnostics to stderr (chosen format, sample bytes consumed, per-stage event counts).

.PP
\fB--version\fP[=false]
	Show version.


